1 0 0 1 56 736.0 Tm (broker taking its own cut than as a benevolent courier.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 722.0 Tm () Tj
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 704.0 Tm (Against the Cooperative Reading) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 690.0 Tm (Popular accounts often describe these networks as forests 'sharing' resources, language that) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 676.0 Tm (imputes intention and mutual benefit. Our data support a more austere reading. The fungus) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 662.0 Tm (extracts carbon from every tree it colonises and redistributes a fraction of it along) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 648.0 Tm (physical gradients, retaining the bulk for its own growth and reproduction.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 634.0 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 56 620.0 Tm (Any benefit to a shaded seedling is incidental to the fungus's metabolism, not its purpose.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 606.0 Tm (This matters for forestry, because management strategies premised on engineering cooperative) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 592.0 Tm (networks rest on a function we could not demonstrate.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 578.0 Tm () Tj
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 560.0 Tm (Conclusion) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 546.0 Tm (Carbon does move between trees through ectomycorrhizal networks, but in quantities and) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 532.0 Tm (directions consistent with ordinary physical transport mediated by a self-interested fungal) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 518.0 Tm (partner. The forest is connected, but it is not, on this evidence, cooperative. Future work) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 504.0 Tm (should quantify how much of the transferred carbon the fungus retains in transit.) Tj
